</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Palos Verdes" /><category term="Clouds" /><category term="Golden Hour" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[It really is a blanket of fog out there. Rare to be in a position to see where the fog stops. 霧に覆われる 本当に霧に包まれている。霧がどこで止まるか見える位置にいるのは珍しい。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2407_DSC_0099_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2407_DSC_0099_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Above the Clouds</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240711/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Above the Clouds" /><published>2024-07-11T00:00:00-07:00</published><updated>2024-07-11T00:00:00-07:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/clouds</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240711/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
At Del Cerro Park on the cliffs of the Palos Verdes Peninsula, looking down at the clouds completely  covering the ocean. In the distance is Catalina Island.
 </p>
  
  <p class="jp">
<span class="title_jp"> 雲の上</span>
